  <front>
   <head>EPITAPH ON A SCHOOLFELLOW.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">LOV'D BANKS, for thee I heave the frequent sigh,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">For thee the solemn tear bedews mine eye;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">No more thy converse blythe shall cheer my day,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Or chase the gloom of anxious thought away.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And art thou, dear associate! art thou gone?</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Long must thy friend his sudden loss bemoan;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">O'er the cold turf where thy pale reliques sleep,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Shall fond Remembrance oft repair to weep.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
